[
    {
        "content": "<p>I would like to define an attribute to use with the simp tactic. However, when I try <code>attribute [foo] my_lemma</code> I get \"unknown attribute [foo]\".</p>\n<p>This page of the Lean reference manual <a href=\"https://leanprover.github.io/reference/other_commands.html#attributes\">https://leanprover.github.io/reference/other_commands.html#attributes</a> says that \"users can declare additional attributes in Lean (see Chapter 7.\" but the link to this \"chapter\" contains a title, two subheadings and nothing else. <span aria-label=\"neutral\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f610\" role=\"img\" title=\"neutral\">:neutral:</span></p>\n<p>Is it actually possible to make user defined attributes in Lean, and if so, how?</p>",
        "id": 234555335,
        "sender_full_name": "Bolton Bailey",
        "timestamp": 1618426856
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is certainly possible -- mathlib adds many attributes to the system, but unfortunately I don't know the details.</p>",
        "id": 234556655,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1618427301
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">@[user_attribute]</span> <span class=\"kd\">meta</span> <span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">my_attribute</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">user_attribute</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"o\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">name</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">descr</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"My own attribute!\"</span> <span class=\"o\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">attribute</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"n\">nat.add_comm</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Look around in the documentation for <code>user_attribute</code> for some more options (cache, parameters, tactics to be executed when you add an attribute).</p>",
        "id": 234556726,
        "sender_full_name": "Floris van Doorn",
        "timestamp": 1618427328
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or search mathlib for <code>@[user_attribute]</code> to see some examples.</p>",
        "id": 234556796,
        "sender_full_name": "Floris van Doorn",
        "timestamp": 1618427360
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks, this is great!</p>",
        "id": 234557019,
        "sender_full_name": "Bolton Bailey",
        "timestamp": 1618427444
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Actually, I tried this example</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">@[user_attribute]</span> <span class=\"kd\">meta</span> <span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">my_attribute</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">user_attribute</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"o\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">name</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">descr</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"My own attribute!\"</span> <span class=\"o\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">attribute</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"n\">nat.add_assoc</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">foo</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">begin</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">simp</span> <span class=\"k\">with</span> <span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">end</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>And got the error \"unknown identifier '<a href=\"http://simp_attr.foo\">simp_attr.foo</a>'\". After some digging in mathlib for an example, I came up with </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">run_cmd</span> <span class=\"n\">mk_simp_attr</span> <span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"n\">bar</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">run_cmd</span> <span class=\"n\">tactic.add_doc_string</span> <span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"n\">simp_attr.bar</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"String\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">attribute</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"n\">nat.add_assoc</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">test2</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">begin</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">simp</span> <span class=\"k\">with</span> <span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">end</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Which throws no errors.</p>",
        "id": 234569683,
        "sender_full_name": "Bolton Bailey",
        "timestamp": 1618432289
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>mathlib has <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/commands.html#mk_simp_attribute\">command#mk_simp_attribute</a> which helps create new custom simp attributes.</p>",
        "id": 234574131,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryan Gin-ge Chen",
        "timestamp": 1618434044
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh my bad, I didn't read carefully enough that you meant simp attributes. In that case you indeed want <code>mk_simp_attribute foo \"My simp attribute\"</code>.</p>",
        "id": 234576092,
        "sender_full_name": "Floris van Doorn",
        "timestamp": 1618434485
    }
]